frameDefinitions: This is an abstract frame for durative activities, in which the Agent enters an ongoing state of the Activity, remains in this state for some Duration of Time, and leaves this state either by finishing or by stopping.
An Agent acts according to a <em>
This frame describes assembly or construction actions, where an Agent joins Components together to form a Created_entity, which is profiled, and hence the object of the verb.
An Agent  places a Component in a Fixed_location so that the Component is attached and interconnected and thereby functional.
This frame contains words which name permanent fixed structures forming an enclosure and providing protection from the elements.
The Creator creates a new entity, the Created_entity, possibly out of Components.
frameExamples: Health authorities say they have put measures into <t>effect</t> in all ports of entry and in centers of provinces.
Jack <t>built</t> a new house out of bricks.
Displays were given an overhaul in the 1950s, with canopies <t>installed</t> above the Christmas counters to allow calendar and gift bows to be displayed. CNI
The baroque <t>church</t>, built in 1635, has a very rich interior
The Libyans were <t>generating</t> arms for export.
listRoleDefinitions: This role identifies the <fen>Activity</fen> in which the  <fen>Agent</fen>  is engaged.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is engaged in the <fen>Activity</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Activity</fen> occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Activity</fen> occurs.
The <fen>Plan</fen> is a goal or purpose that the <fen>Agent</fen> carries out.

The <fen>Agent</fen>, often an institution or governmental organization, puts a <fen>Plan</fen> into effect. The Agent is generally a primary participant in the <fen>Plan</fen>, but a separate <fen>Focal_participant</fen> may be specified.
This role describes the medium through which a plan was executed.  It may occur in the same syntactic position as the Agent.
The <fen>Time</fen> at which the Agent puts the <fen>Plan</fen> into effect.

The <fen>Place</fen> at which the <fen>Plan</fen> is or is not operational.

[CHANGE: or, place where agent puts into effect? 2 fes?]
The <fen>Agent</fen> builds a <fen>Created_entity</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Components</fen> that form the <fen>Created_entity</fen>.
<fen>Created_entity</fen> identifies the entity that is created in the act of building.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the building occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the building occurs.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is the person (or other force) that installs the <fen>Component</fen>.
The <fen>Component</fen> is the object that is placed in a <fen>Fixed_location</fen>.
The <fen>Fixed_location</fen> is the location where the <fen>Component</fen> is placed and to which it is attached so as to be useful.
The time period in which the <fen>Component</fen> is installed.
The <fen>Place</fen> indicates where the installation occurs.
The entity built by the <fen>Builder</fen> which has some <fen>Function</fen>.
The building's location.
The Creator creates a created entity.
This role identifies the entity that the Agent intentionally creates.
This role identifes the Time when an Agent intentionally creates a new entity.
This role identifies the place ehere the Agent intentionally creates the new entity.
listRoleExamples: The policy will be implemented <fex>by a new computer system</fex>.
Jack built  a new house <fex>out of old bricks</fex>.
Jack built a new house <fex>early in the morning</fex>.
Jack built a new house <fex>in a glade</fex>.
<fex>John</fex> installed it last night on my Gentoo system and everything is going fine so far.

I assembled the fuel tank using a vent line and a supply line, and then I installed
the tank <fex>in the fuselage</fex>.
When we installed our hood <fex>last month</fex>, the folks at Dallas Auto Body painted our roll pan at the same time.
When I installed the server <fex>there</fex> last winter they only had two rows of racks, mostly empty.
